(499, 1, '2015-09-24 02:45:48', '2015-09-24 02:45:48', 'As a production worker (also known as a process operative or factory worker) you''d be involved in manufacturing goods and parts in industries like pharmaceuticals, food and drink, construction and engineering.\n\nIf you''ve got good practical skills, and you can work quickly and accurately, you might enjoy this job.\n\nIn this job you''ll need to work well in a team. You''ll also need the ability to concentrate over long periods.\n\nYou may not need any set qualifications to become a production worker, although some GCSEs, including English and maths may give you an advantage when looking for work. You may be able to get into this job through an apprenticeship.\n- See more at: https://nationalcareersservice.direct.gov.uk/advice/planning/jobprofiles/Pages/productionworker(manufacturing).aspx#sthash.VPtlRF05.dpuf', 'Production', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '495-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:45:48', '2015-09-24 02:45:48', '', 495, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/495-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(500, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'Apprenticeships provide practice-based training for people who want to learn new skills and gain qualifications while working. As a Laing O’Rourke apprentice you will work with experienced tradespeople and construction professionals while completing a structured programme of study. All of this will allow you to develop a broad set of technical and trade skills, while achieving a recognised qualification. On completion, apprentices can choose from three career pathways: Remain on site in a trades-based role Continue into further education and progress into supervision / management. Find out more about our European Entry here and our Australian Entry here. Applications for UK based apprenticeships are now open. Click here to search for apprentice roles. – See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/european-careers/apprentices.aspx#sthash.06emaiOp.dpuf', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '500', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=500', 1, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(501, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'Laing O’Rourke is committed to being an equal opportunities employer: an employer that maintains the highest standard of employment practice and one which aims to employ a workforce that reflects the diverse society in which we live and work. This policy forms part of our global policy framework, underpinned by our Global Code of Conduct.In order to provide a diverse and inclusive workplace and achieve our objectives, we commit to: • Act as role models with values and behaviours which foster workforce diversity • Recognise and reflect diversity and inclusion • Create a supportive environment where everyone can reach their full potential by ensuring policies and procedures support the attraction, selection, retention and promotion of people from a diverse range of candidates on the basis of skills and merit • Identify and remove barriers that hinder the achievement of a diverse and talented workforce • Draw the attention of all those responsible for recruitment, selection, training, grievance or disciplinary or dismissal decisions to this policy; • Provide our people with access to the learning and development opportunities that are appropriate for their role • Communicate with, consult and educate, all employees in respect of their own responsibilities and the Company’s…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '501', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=501', 2, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(502, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'The vast variety of roles we offer reflects the breadth of skills required to run an organisation such as ours. Naturally we seek specialists across the spectrum of project delivery disciplines – including planning, procurement, engineering, commercial management, etc. We also require qualified professionals to staff our office-based services. These encompass everything from cost planning to corporate communications, business development to building information modelling. We work hard to ensure all our people benefit from structured career support – and get the training they need to reach their potential. This includes full-time development programmes as well as shorter on-the-job learning modules. But we also believe that learning shouldn’t be restricted to the classroom. So in addition to these more formal routes, we are committed to creating a working environment that allows you to build your skills that little bit further every day – simply by doing your job. – See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/european-careers/experienced-professionals.aspx#sthash.4G5nxfsD.dpuf', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '502', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=502', 3, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(503, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'To continue delivering the world-class buildings and infrastructure Laing O’Rourke has become renowned for, we’re looking for today’s brightest graduates to create the next generation of engineering and construction talent. As a Laing O’Rourke graduate, your capabilities will be recognised and rewarded. Most importantly, you will be encouraged to continue learning throughout your career. You will be stretched, challenged and supported by a business that views your professional development as a priority. What does the programme involve? Our graduate programme combines practical experience, technical learning and professional development. Diverse on-the-job experience will be complemented by an engaging series of learning modules, helping you to build the right blend of personal and professional skills. The programme is offered globally, lasting 32 months in our Europe hub and 24 months in our Australia hub. You will be mentored by experienced leaders, and enjoy strong support from line managers and a large peer group network. We will work closely with you to develop clear career goals, expand your skills and assist you in working towards the relevant chartership. On completion, you will continue to benefit from ongoing support from our graduate development team and a network of business contacts, as you move into…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '503', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=503', 4, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(504, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'We believe people perform best when they have a clear sense of direction. For this reason we make sure all our employees are able to build the capabilities they need to achieve their aspirations. Last year we invested more than £21 million in training, development and education. We offer a range of programmes to meet our trades-based and professional skills requirements.This includes a dedicated online training portal which gives employees access to a wide range of e-learning courses. Those with the potential to fast-track into leadership roles can select from a structured series of full-time courses. Currently we have over 700 staff on these programmes. For more information, click on the relevant link below: Apprenticeships Sponsored learning Graduates and masters But, progression isn’t just about training. At Laing O’Rourke we make sure that all our people benefit from structured career support. We expect all managers to work with their employees to help them achieve their aspirations. A clear way forward We have developed a set of ‘career toolkits’ covering a variety of job roles. These contain detailed information on the experience and qualifications required at each stage of development. This gives everyone a clear view of where they are and…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '504', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=504', 5, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(505, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'You can search for job opportunities through the link below and will need to create an on-line account with us in order to submit an application. Click here to launch our dedicated global careers website Click here to launch our dedicated website for construction workforce positions in Australia Applicants who applied for a role with Laing O’Rourke prior to 1st July 2013 You may find that due to systems development at Laing O’Rourke your existing Candidate Profile may now have expired. For any future applications you will be required to create a new profile via the link above. We apologise for any inconvenience but we are constantly striving to improve processes for both our current and prospective employees. Thank you Human Capital team   Equality, Diversity and Inclusion Policy Laing O’Rourke is committed to being an equal opportunities employer: an employer that maintains the highest standard of employment practice and one which aims to employ a workforce that reflects the diverse society in which we live and work. This policy forms part of our global policy framework, underpinned by our Global Code of Conduct. In order to provide a diverse and inclusive workplace and achieve our objectives, we commit to:…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '505', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=505', 6, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(506, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'Our sponsored learning schemes allow you to combine higher education with on-the-job experience – giving you the edge as you enter the world of work. If you’re eager to make a start on the career ladder – but don’t want to miss out on the benefits of a formal education – why not consider our ‘cadet’ programme? Alternatively, our ‘scholarship’ programme lets full-time students earn while they learn – giving you the opportunity to put academic theory into practice. Applications for the UK based Cadet Programme are now open. Click here to search for cadet roles.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '506', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=506', 7, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(507, 1, '2015-09-24 02:48:28', '2015-09-24 02:48:28', 'We work hard to create an environment that brings out the best in our people. So as a Laing O’Rourke employee you can be sure your career is in good hands. Every day thousands of people across the world go to work at our offices and on our projects. So what made them choose us over other great companies? Challenging you to achieve your ambitions We think people should enjoy what they do. That’s why we believe in building careers – not just creating jobs. We work with all our people to help them make the most of their talents. Through on-the-job learning, we’ll make sure you’re stretching yourself that little bit further every day. While our broad-ranging training and development programmes will give you the skills to take on evermore challenging roles. Giving you job satisfaction Our people are among the most passionate and committed in the industry. How do we know this? Because every year, through our staff survey, we track ‘employee engagement’ levels – and every year, without fail, we rank among the highest of any global company. Our employee engagement score is essentially a measure of how satisfied our people are in their jobs. For this…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '507', '', '', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '2015-09-24 02:49:58', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/?p=507', 8, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0);
