(548, 1, '2015-09-24 07:05:22', '2015-09-24 07:05:22', '<div id="intro"><p>An alliance featuring Laing O''Rourke has begun the construction of Perth''s newest transport link - See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/media/news-releases/2015/stadium-station-kicks-off.aspx#sthash.AkTaqWJc.dpufases.</p><div>\nAn alliance featuring Laing O''Rourke has begun the construction of Perth''s newest transport link\nPerth Stadium Station Transport Minister Dean Nalder on site\n\nWest Australian Transport Minister, the Hon. Dean Nalder MLA, last week visited Perth''s Stadium Station site to officially launch the first construction works.\n\nBeing delivered by an alliance of Laing O''Rourke, AECOM and the Public Transport Authority, the project will transform the Burswood precinct and deliver the city''s second-largest transport interchange.\n- See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/media/news-releases/2015/stadium-station-kicks-off.aspx#sthash.AkTaqWJc.dpuf', 'Stadium Station kicks off', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '537-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 07:05:22', '2015-09-24 07:05:22', '', 537, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/537-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(549, 1, '2015-09-24 07:07:19', '2015-09-24 07:07:19', '<div id="intro"><p>Laing O’Rourke has signed a contract with Transport for New South Wales that will see Australia’s largest, privately owned engineering enterprise deliver major accessibility upgrades at four busy stations across the Greater Sydney region, including:</p></div>\n<ul>\n	<li>Penrith</li>\n	<li>Flemington</li>\n	<li>Wentworth Falls, and</li>\n	<li>Heathcote</li>\n</ul>\nThe improvements include new lifts, concourse bridges, walkways, staircases, canopies, platform modifications and improved lighting and train notification systems.\n\nThe work will also ensure that all four stations provide easy access for people with a disability and are compliant with the Disability Discrimination Act.\n\nLaing O’Rourke Southern Region Director Mark Dimmock said the company had a proven record in the delivery of major infrastructure projects with Transport for NSW.\n\n“We are currently engaged on a number of projects across the Sydney Trains network, all of which are delivering an improved experience for commuters,” Mr Dimmock said.\n\n“We have the skills, experience and expertise from working closely with the Government, understanding TfNSW''s requirements, to deliver the project within the desired timeframe and with the best possible result for commuters.”\n\nLaing O’Rourke’s work for Transport for NSW includes network-wide upgrades through the billion dollar Novo Rail Alliance, the Auburn Stabling Project, the Sydney Light Rail early works programme, the Wickham transport interchange and the $100million upgrade of Wynyard, one of Sydney''s busiest CBD stations.\n- See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/media/news-releases/2015/easy-access-station-upgrades-for-sydney-commuters.aspx#sthash.VCzv8J9b.dpuf', 'Easy Access station upgrades for Sydney commuters', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '533-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 07:07:19', '2015-09-24 07:07:19', '', 533, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/533-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
