(587, 1, '2015-09-28 05:04:46', '2015-09-28 05:04:46', '<div id="intro"><p>Established in 1987, the company then known as Omega International Coatings Pty Ltd; was a small light industrial paint company based in Sydney. Its only manufacturing facility was in Mount Druitt, NSW which produced industrial paints, varnishes and thinners.</p></div>\r\n\r\nOmega International Coatings Pty Ltd continued its exponential growth and in 2007 acquired Apco Coatings (subsidiary of multinational paint manufacturer Asian Paints) and then broadened their scope into automotive, decorative and specialty paints.\r\n\r\nFrom a production capacity of 170 tonnes/week in 2015, the organisation has come a long way to further expand operations by entering into the paint service and applications sector. After acquiring paint contracting company Omega Painting Pty Ltd in 2011, the group revamped their marketing image under one simple banner “Omega Industries", releasing Australia''s first vertically integrated paint company with the new "Supply &amp; Apply" concept.\r\n\r\nToday, having solely used and developed the name and trademark Omega Industries and all its variants in Australia, is now a commercially recognised coatings business. With the Head Office in Sydney, the company manufactures and markets a range of decorative and industrial paint products and application services under various product brands.\r\n\r\nIts operations spread across the length &amp; breadth of the country. There are two manufacturing facilities in Australia as well as distribution centres, and several regional and area offices.', 'Snapshot of our history', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '159-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-28 05:04:46', '2015-09-28 05:04:46', '', 159, 'http://111.93.163.213/Omega/php/159-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(588, 1, '2015-09-28 05:13:31', '2015-09-28 05:13:31', '<div class="clearfix" id="contentWrapper">\r\n    <h1>Buildings</h1><div id="intro"><p>Laing O’Rourke’s building construction teams share a common goal &ndash; to create a built environment that enhances people’s lives.&nbsp; We are well known for constructing elegant structures that perform to the highest standards, creating lasting value for asset owners.</p></div><div class="twoCols"><div class="col"><div class="text"><h2 class="columnMainHeading">Overview</h2><p>Our collaborative approach through early design involvement, engineering expertise and integrated delivery ensures we are able to complete complex projects to exacting time, cost and quality standards, safely and sustainably.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAcross key business sectors we design, procure, manage, construct, refurbish and maintain commercial offices, data centres, industrial facilities and science and research centres.</p>\r\n<h2>Lifestyle and Leisure</h2>\r\n<p>We provide engineering, construction, project management and operational maintenance services for Lifestyle markets covering <strong>hotels, residential, retail, sports </strong>and <strong>leisure</strong> in Europe, Middle East and Australia.</p>\r\n<p>Many developments - such as <strong>sporting stadia</strong> or <strong>convention centres</strong> - attract intense public scrutiny. Clients need to know they are working with a partner who will protect their reputation through flawless delivery to often immovable deadlines.&nbsp; We understand the multiple functions these facilities have to serve and we apply our in-depth knowledge of complex sports and multi-purpose venues to maximise return on the clients’ investments.</p>\r\n<p>We have delivered some of the world''s most iconic lifestyle complexes, such as the <a href="/our-work/all-projects/atlantis.aspx">Atlantis Hotel in Dubai</a>,&nbsp;the convention centres of <a href="/our-work/all-projects/brisbane-convention-and-exhibition-centre.aspx">Brisbane</a>, the Gold Coast, <a href="/our-work/all-projects/darwin-convention-and-exhibition-centre.aspx">Darwin</a> and Hong Kong. We were the lead member of the consortium managing delivery of major elements of the <a href="/our-work/all-projects/london-2012-olympics-and-paralympics.aspx">London 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Park</a>, heralded as the most successful sporting event in UK history. </p>\r\n<p>Our European residential housing operation, Explore Living, builds on our long-standing tradition of innovation in the housing market dating back to the early years of the John Laing Construction business, and has won numerous awards for the quality of its developments.</p>\r\n<h2>Social Infrastructure</h2>\r\n<p>We are a leading supplier of Social Infrastructure for governments and private-sector clients. </p>\r\n<p>Our presence in the <strong>education</strong> sector is particularly strong. We understand the need for early collaboration with all stakeholders to balance the interests between creating an inspiring learning environment, while maximising the capital investment.</p>\r\n<p>Healthcare projects are amongst the most complex and time critical in construction. As one of the world’s leading providers of state-of-the-art <strong>hospitals</strong> that meet the innovative needs of the healthcare industry, Laing O’Rourke’s advanced offsite construction techniques and expertise in systems integration assure projects are engineered to exceptional standards of quality and craftsmanship. We are at the forefront of Health Authority Private Finance Initiative (PFI) or Public Private Partnership (PPP) based procurement initiatives, and are heavily engaged in UK and Australian Government programmes.&nbsp; </p>\r\n<p>Our leading Building Information Modelling and offsite manufacturing capabilities enable faster construction and greater standardisation of core components - essential to meeting the demands of Governments striving to deliver schools and hospitals faster, better, for less, while ensuring the durability of such heavily utilised facilities over their lifetime. </p>\r\n<p>We are increasingly recognised as the preferred delivery partner for the <strong>defence</strong> and <strong>law and order</strong> sectors, with a proven capacity to meet the exacting quality and security specifications demanded by the armed forces and judicial services. Our portfolio ranges from maximum security military communications and intelligence facilities to <strong>courthouses, prisons and law enforcement projects</strong>. Our track record to date demonstrates our capabilities to manage the construction and commissioning of fully operational and secure facilities, optimising innovative pre-assembly solutions to overcome complicated security challenges.</p>\r\n<p>We have a core capability in the social or remote Indigenous <strong>housing</strong> and urban regeneration markets. Our innovative application of new construction techniques embodied in our Design for Manufacture and Assembly (DfMA) approach allows us to provide smarter, cost-effective solutions that deliver higher quality in less time.</p></div></div><div class="col"><div><div class="featuredStory clearfix"><h2>Sector facts</h2><div class="storyBox clearfix"><div id="storyTextWrapper"><p>Dagenham Park Church of England School, London &ndash; 70% of the building constructed off site, resulting in an incredibly fast and efficient build programme, creating one of the most environmentally sustainable schools across the UK.<br><br>Centre Hospitalier de l’Université de Montréal, Canada &ndash; As one of the world’s largest healthcare projects , the CAD$2.1bn deal represents the most valuable social infrastructure PPP scheme in Canada’s history.<br><br>The Moorebank Units Relocation (MUR) project for the Australian Department of Defence is the military’s largest capital works program since World War II, and will decommission and relocate one strategic facility, unlock vital industrial lands in southern Sydney, and build on Laing O’Rourke’s long-term relationship with defence projects in Australia. <br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="footerQuickLinks hasProjectsCarousel"><div class="col"><a href="/contact-us.aspx" id="contact"><span>Contact us</span>about your project</a></div><div class="col last"><a id="view" href="/our-work/our-sectors.aspx"><span>View</span>all sectors</a></div></div><div id="projectsRelativeWrapper"><h2>Projects from this sector</h2><div class="slider_wrapper"><div class="clearfix ryslider" id="projectsSlider" style="left: 0px; width: 10320px;"><div class="slide-1 sliderContent active" style="left: 0px;"><header><div class="headings"><h2>Cannon Place</h2><h3>London. UK</h3><a href="/our-work/all-projects/cannon-place.aspx" class="button">Discover</a></div></header><img width="860" height="251" alt="" src="/~/media/lor/images/banners_1200x350/cannonplace2.jpg?bc=Black&amp;h=251&amp;la=en&amp;w=860"></div><div class="slide-2 sliderContent" style="left: 860px;"><header><div class="headings"><h2>Doubletree Hotel</h2><h3>London. UK</h3><a href="/our-work/all-projects/doubletree-hotel.aspx" class="button">Discover</a></div></header><img width="860" height="251" alt="" src="/~/media/lor/images/banners_1200x350/doubletree_minthotel.jpg?bc=Black&amp;h=251&amp;la=en&amp;w=860"></div><div class="slide-3 sliderContent" style="left: 1720px;"><header><div class="headings"><h2>One Hyde Park</h2><h3>London. UK</h3><a href="/our-work/all-projects/one-hyde-park.aspx" class="button">Discover</a></div></header><img width="860" height="251" alt="" src="/~/media/lor/images/banners_1200x350/onehydepark2.jpg?bc=Black&amp;h=251&amp;la=en&amp;w=860"></div><div class="slide-4 sliderContent" style="left: 2580px;"><header><div class="headings"><h2>Heathrow Terminal 5</h2><h3>London. UK</h3><a href="/our-work/all-projects/heathrow-terminal-5.aspx" class="button">Discover</a></div></header><img width="860" height="251" alt="" 