(4, 4, 'sectors', 'Overview\r\n\r\nOur collaborative approach through early design involvement, engineering expertise and integrated delivery ensures we are able to complete complex projects to exacting time, cost and quality standards, safely and sustainably.\r\n\r\nAcross key business sectors we design, procure, manage, construct, refurbish and maintain commercial offices, data centres, industrial facilities and science and research centres.\r\nLifestyle and Leisure\r\n\r\nWe provide engineering, construction, project management and operational maintenance services for Lifestyle markets covering hotels, residential, retail, sports and leisure in Europe, Middle East and Australia.\r\n\r\nMany developments - such as sporting stadia or convention centres - attract intense public scrutiny. Clients need to know they are working with a partner who will protect their reputation through flawless delivery to often immovable deadlines.  We understand the multiple functions these facilities have to serve and we apply our in-depth knowledge of complex sports and multi-purpose venues to maximise return on the clients’ investments.\r\n\r\nWe have delivered some of the world''s most iconic lifestyle complexes, such as the Atlantis Hotel in Dubai, the convention centres of Brisbane, the Gold Coast, Darwin and Hong Kong. We were the lead member of the consortium managing delivery of major elements of the London 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Park, heralded as the most successful sporting event in UK history.\r\n\r\nOur European residential housing operation, Explore Living, builds on our long-standing tradition of innovation in the housing market dating back to the early years of the John Laing Construction business, and has won numerous awards for the quality of its developments.\r\nSocial Infrastructure\r\n\r\nWe are a leading supplier of Social Infrastructure for governments and private-sector clients.\r\n\r\nOur presence in the education sector is particularly strong. We understand the need for early collaboration with all stakeholders to balance the interests between creating an inspiring learning environment, while maximising the capital investment.\r\n\r\nHealthcare projects are amongst the most complex and time critical in construction. As one of the world’s leading providers of state-of-the-art hospitals that meet the innovative needs of the healthcare industry, Laing O’Rourke’s advanced offsite construction techniques and expertise in systems integration assure projects are engineered to exceptional standards of quality and craftsmanship. We are at the forefront of Health Authority Private Finance Initiative (PFI) or Public Private Partnership (PPP) based procurement initiatives, and are heavily engaged in UK and Australian Government programmes. \r\n\r\nOur leading Building Information Modelling and offsite manufacturing capabilities enable faster construction and greater standardisation of core components - essential to meeting the demands of Governments striving to deliver schools and hospitals faster, better, for less, while ensuring the durability of such heavily utilised facilities over their lifetime.\r\n\r\nWe are increasingly recognised as the preferred delivery partner for the defence and law and order sectors, with a proven capacity to meet the exacting quality and security specifications demanded by the armed forces and judicial services. Our portfolio ranges from maximum security military communications and intelligence facilities to courthouses, prisons and law enforcement projects. Our track record to date demonstrates our capabilities to manage the construction and commissioning of fully operational and secure facilities, optimising innovative pre-assembly solutions to overcome complicated security challenges.\r\n\r\nWe have a core capability in the social or remote Indigenous housing and urban regeneration markets. Our innovative application of new construction techniques embodied in our Design for Manufacture and Assembly (DfMA) approach allows us to provide smarter, cost-effective solutions that deliver higher quality in less time.\r\n- See more at: http://www.laingorourke.com/our-work/our-sectors/buildings.aspx#sthash.ok4wIKcV.dpuf', 0, 6),
(5, 5, 'sectors', '<h3>Overview</h3>\r\n\r\nWe have managed numerous projects in isolated regions across Australia, helping us to build an impressive bank of practical knowledge of the requirements relating to the development of world-class resources infrastructure, particularly integrated pit-to-port services to service the booming export markets.\r\nLaing O’Rourke’s highly experienced mining engineers and project delivery personnel ensure we pay detailed attention at the early planning stages of every project to assure constructability. Our proven track record working collaboratively with some of the world’s largest mining and resource companies underpins our ability to provide clients with cost effective solutions.\r\n\r\n<h3>Broad capabilities</h3>\r\n\r\nOur unique in-house design strength, as well as world-leading technology partners, enables us to deliver integrated materials handling systems, dump stations, conveyor systems, crushing and screening plants, supporting infrastructure including roads, rail loops, dams, water retaining structures and pipelines, to processing and washery solutions, stockpiling, stacking and reclaiming, electrical and control systems and load-out facilities.\r\n\r\nOn the port side, participants in the materials exporting industries have all drawn on our specialist expertise for dredging, civil works, berth design and construction, and the erecting and commissioning of materials-based ship-loading facilities.\r\nIn delivering mining infrastructure for public and private sector clients, Laing O’Rourke has developed expertise in creating innovative solutions via different contractual arrangements, including construct only, design and construct and engineer, procure and construct (EPC), through self delivery, alliances and joint ventures. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Full Service offering</h3>\r\n\r\nOur in-house Austrak, Redispan and Select businesses are also bringing innovative thinking to our full service offering, with greater use of offsite manufacturing of modularised products to drive time and cost efficiencies in the installation of higher quality resource handling infrastructure like railway lines and mineral conveyors.\r\n\r\nOur unique focus on worker safety and welfare is made possible through our direct employment model which provides greater control in the construction phases, alongside our expertise in building and maintaining state-of-the-art accommodation villages.', 0, 2),
